01

We lost 266 men in an instant

The 19th, January twenty-six. Wednesday.

Is still a rare environmental protection under the blue water and blue sky.

Factories don't smoke, cars don't run through the streets, that's how it is.

A total of 394 new confirmed cases, 114 new deaths (108 in Hubei, 1 each in Hebei, Shanghai, Fujian, Shandong, Yunnan and Shaanxi) and 1,277 new suspected cases were reported nationwide Thursday.

As of the 19th, there were 56,303 confirmed cases (including 11,864 serious cases) , 16,155 cured cases, 2118 dead cases, 74,576 confirmed cases and 4922 suspected cases.

There were 349 newly confirmed cases in Hubei (615 in Wuhan, 13 in Xiantao and 10 in Jingmen and Xianning) . Down for the third day in a row. In the past, there were 1933 cases (16 days) , 1807 cases (17 days) and 1693 cases (18 days) . This time it was a nice drop.

There were 108 new deaths (88 in Wuhan) , 49,665 confirmed cases (37,994 in Wuhan) and 11,178 severe cases (9,689 in Wuhan) .

There were 2029 cumulative deaths (1585 in Wuhan) and 62031 confirmed cases (45027 in Wuhan) .

On the 19th, there were 45 newly confirmed cases in China except Hubei, which was the 16th consecutive day of decline. There were 890(3 days) , 731(4 days) , 707(5 days) , 696(6 days) , 558(7 days) , 509(8 days) , 444(9 days) , 381(10 days) , 377(11 days) , 312(12 days) , 267(13 days) , 221(14 days) , 166(15 days) , 115(16 days) , there were 79 cases (17 days) and 56 cases (18 days) .

Moreover, from 0 to 24 o'clock on the 19th, Liaoning, Fujian, Shanxi, Shanghai, Jiangsu, Guizhou, Ningxia, Inner Mongolia, Qinghai and other places reported 0 newly confirmed cases of coronary pneumonia; from 12 to 24 o'clock on the 19th, no new cases of coronary pneumonia were confirmed in Yunnan and Guizhou, and no new cases were confirmed in Gansu from 20:00 am to 20:00 pm on 18th to 19th.

As we all know, the National Health Commission released 19 new cases of pneumonia, new Wuhan confirmed 615 cases, and the province added 349 cases.

Where did 266 people go?

The Hubei Provincial Health Commission's response was swift. On the 18th, the National Health Commission issued a notice on the printing and distribution of the sixth edition of the COVID-19's diagnosis and treatment plan, as opposed to the fifth edition, hubei province-specific clinical diagnostic case categories were cancelled, retaining only confirmed and suspected cases.

In order to coordinate the adjustment of the diagnosis and treatment plan, some cities and prefectures organized an expert group to consult again the previously reported clinical diagnosed cases, and through a comprehensive analysis of the epidemiological history, clinical symptoms and laboratory test results of the cases, some of the previously reported cases were found not to meet the definition of confirmed cases, and it was decided to revise them to other diseases or to classify them as suspected cases, which were reported directly in the pandemic network.

As a result, the number of people in Wuhan remained the same, the number of people in other cities and states decreased, and the number in the whole province decreased.

Some netizens took the opportunity to talk to me and the Bureau of Statistics. "Lay down the gun. ".

But I do need to say more.

Here's why:

In the previous edition, the number of clinically diagnosed cases in Hubei Province was added, mainly taking into account the actual situation in Hubei Province, due to the limited supply of nucleic acid kits and detection capacity, and the fact that a certain proportion of patients with NCP have negative nucleic acid detection, in order to receive treatment as early as possible and to prevent the spread of the virus as far as possible, a special increase in the number of clinically diagnosed cases in Hubei Province is equivalent to treatment of confirmed cases, but nucleic acid testing is still required after the admission of clinically diagnosed cases, final diagnosis.

At the moment, this portion is not nucleic acid tested, but the cases with lung imaging features are nearly digested.

According to statistics, the newly confirmed cases in Wuhan in general after February 13, five consecutive days maintained a downward trend. In the last three days, the daily increase was maintained at 1,600-1,700, which was relatively steady.

At the same time, Wuhan's nucleic acid detection capacity has also been greatly enhanced, at present, Wuhan daily detection capacity can reach 10,000 to 13,000 people.

In this case, nucleic acid testing on the speed of diagnosis has been very small, therefore, the province on the unity of a standard. To cancel the data from the clinical records.

Things are always changing.

On News 1 + 1, which aired Sunday night, Bai Yansong called Chinese Academy of Engineering, the Vice Dean of the hospital, again 14 days later, a specialist in breathing and critical care medicine.

14 questions, several of them crucial.

For example, how many patients are there in Wuhan? Did you feel the discharge?

Wang Chen: It is very important to touch the row. At present, it has become more than 90% . But the exact number of patients is unclear, and the number of cases diagnosed each day is real.

Could the new coronavirus co-exist with us for a long time?

Wang Chen: unlike SARS, SARS is very contagious and pathogenic. It kills the host quickly and the virus itself is not easy to survive. New coronary pneumonia could turn into a chronic disease, co-existing with humans like the flu. In this regard, we should make corresponding preparations from the aspects of clinical diagnosis, treatment, production and prevention.

This view was also confirmed at a press conference in Wuhan.

On the evening of the 19th, Tong Chaohui, deputy director of Beijing Chaoyang Hospital, Jiang Rongmeng, chief physician of the Second Department of Infection, Beijing Temple of Earth Hospital, and Wu Anhua, director of the Central South University, were among the experts of the Medical Treatment Group of the Central Guidance Group, they agreed that the new coronavirus was highly infectious and more difficult to treat than SARS, but the mortality rate was lower than SARS.

Different from the SARS patients, most of the new severe pneumonia patients are over 50 years old, and most of them have cardiovascular and cerebrovascular diseases. In the course of disease, new pneumonia patients progress faster, hypoxia development is obvious, if not well controlled will soon develop to respiratory failure.

That's why the death toll topped 2,000 within a month.

As of 12:00 on the 17th, Hubei Province has received 11.543 billion yuan in donations. The relevant person in charge said that as some medical prevention and control materials in Hubei Province are still in short supply, the community is urged to continue to support the following most urgently needed materials: medical protective clothing, medical surgical masks, medical protective masks, etc. . I hope we can continue to get help.

More than 1,200 medical teams from Shanghai, Jilin and Heilongjiang continued to gather in Hubei on Sunday.

In fact, six provincial-level cadres from other provinces are helping out across Hubei.

Yang Dongqi, deputy secretary of the Shandong Provincial Party Committee, Sun Jiye, deputy governor, and Zhang Jian, vice chairman of the Hunan Provincial Committee of the Chinese People's Political Consultative Conference, led more than 1,000 health care workers from the two provinces to help Huanggang.

Lu Zhiyuan, deputy director of the Provincial People's Congress, was the commander in chief of the Anti Epidemic Forward Command in Hainan Province. On the afternoon of February 14, he set out from Haikou with his headquarters.

Li Jinke, member of the Standing Committee of the Party Committee and head of the Propaganda Department of Ningxia Autonomous Region, went to Hubei on February 15 to serve as the commander of the front-line command of Ningxia's support for Hubei's epidemic prevention and control.

Hui Jianlin, a newly appointed member of the party group of the Jiangsu Provincial Government and former party secretary of Zhenjiang, led a team to Huangshi, the province's counterpart.

02

Make a declaration of war

After three days of grid-like investigation, all the districts have handed in papers successfully. This is what the public will be waiting for.

On the evening of the 19th, the new Wuhan Pneumonia Epidemic Prevention and Control Headquarters is holding a video dispatch meeting. Secretary Wang Zhonglin requested all district party committee secretaries, district heads to sign a "responsibility certificate" , confirmed cases are not a home and other issues to undertake commitments, the next step, if there is an oversight, immediately accountability. "We can not take back what we have said, " he said, reminding cadres at all levels to ensure that the figures are true, that the Seek truth from facts are not false.

In the face of this vigorous action, netizens applauded.

My friend said: "War" The basic working principles, there is no "war" experience of the key position of the "key man" , are often "defeated" . In wartime, once such a commander-in-chief is in place, he may be "corrected" in time; but in times of Peace and development, a large number of cadres promoted to commander-in-chief who have not fought hard will, in the face of the greatest censure, bungle their aircraft, eventually, a key commander grows up and ends up.

Whether the cadres are qualified or not depends on their ability to deal with emergencies.

This three-day dragnet-type screening, can be described as "textbook-style" .

This gives us an inspiration, in the face of the virus, we need to have a professional medical team, a strong social control team. If the police force in Wuhan is not enough, they can transfer to other provinces.

Therefore, to change a name, the establishment of "earthquake disaster relief and rescue team" , in the face of the virus, as in the face of the earthquake, flood, as well as the formation of the team to pull out.

Of course, I don't want it to happen again.

On the 19th, the Traffic Control Department issued a notice to comprehensively strengthen traffic control in the urban area of Wuhan, all vehicles are prohibited from entering the area except those used in the war of "epidemic disease" , official vehicles, public transportation, vehicles used by medical and nursing personnel, vehicles used for transporting necessities of daily life, and special vehicles such as rescue, fire fighting, emergency rescue, environmental sanitation and police vehicles.

This is the real "closure" . The old "car restriction" was weak.

On August 18th Zhong Nanshan stressed the importance of keeping the drains free from blockage.

A team has previously found a new coronavirus in feces. The new coronavirus does not necessarily spread through the digestive tract, Zhong Nanshan said, "but because pollutants dry up in the sewers and spread through the air and aerosols that people breathe in and cause infections. "

He again through the media, good drainage and clean, minimize the risk of infection.

Since January 29, when Wuhan launched the disinfection of drainage facilities and sewage treatment facilities, as of February 18, the city's districts and units have sent a total of 6,520 people, a total of 1,963.58 tons of disinfectant. All the 26 Sewage Treatment in the city were disinfected by sodium hypochlorite 24 hours continuously. The accumulated amount of intensified disinfection of tail water was 1777.36 tons, and the amount of disinfection of sludge was 33.69 tons.

After the complete closure of the community, but also at home "alone" of the small animals do? Sometimes, standing on the 12th floor terrace, you can hear the cat's call clearly in the bushes, which is heartrending.

Du Fan, president of the Wuhan Small Animal Protection Association, led volunteers to provide free assistance to small animals stranded in Wuhan from January 26. So far, the association has visited more than 1,400 times and rescued more than 5,000 animals.

However, on the 17th, with the Wuhan Community more and more strict control, volunteers have been unable to travel, also can not enter the community where the help, the work will have to be suspended.

"You could go out once every three days, but it's basically harder to go out when the upgrade notice comes out. But help is still coming. Now we get thirty calls a day. Many of them we have already visited once before, but it is time to replenish water and food,"said Du.

To this end, Du fan began to help people in the field as far as possible to find neighbors help each other. "We have a 'Wuhan micro-neighborhood' APP and a 'Neighborhood Help: pet mutual help platform' website, and all we can do now is bring help seekers to these platforms and ask them to look for neighbors in the same neighborhood to help. "

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Pets in the house, alive or dead, are a nuisance.

So, we need to think about this. If you go out, you should put your pet's money in a pet agency. And these surrogacy centers are supposed to be in the suburbs.

This is a hard lesson.

03

More caring for health care workers

More than 3,000 health care workers across the country have been infected with the new coronavirus, but most were infected before Jan. 30, a National Health Commission panel said. At present, the medical teams from all over Hubei Province have not found any cases of infection among the medical staff, which indicates that infection among the medical staff can be avoided through effective protective measures.

Visible, remote + protection, can avoid the invasion of viruses.

It's easy for the average person to get dressed, but it's not easy for the medical staff in the hospital.

According to the standard, there are 13 steps in the process of wearing protective equipment. After washing hands, first put on a medical protective mask and a disposable work cap, then change into work shoes and socks, put on separate work clothes, medical protective clothing, and wear inner latex gloves, add disposable hats, surgical masks and goggles. If necessary, wear disposable clothing, and finally put on the outer layer of latex gloves, boots and overshoes. It takes about 15 minutes.

The core principle of a full suit is to keep every inch of your skin out of the air.

A pair of goggles, two face masks, three layers of clothing, two layers of gloves, two pairs of shoe covers... sitting still is already sweating, and these paramedics have to wear such a well-equipped clothes, a whole day's work.

Now, medical staff can also have a late night snack. The aid-han medical team has opened 27 freemasons in each station, and the medical team members can get 50 kinds of goods free of charge at any time by scanning the code.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Many places have put in place policies to give preferential treatment to medical personnel, and this is due. Fuzhou, Jiangxi, on the other hand, is ten points higher.

Fuzhou, Jiangxi Education and Sports Bureau notice: The city's first-line medical staff directly involved in the treatment of patients with new crown pneumonia, supporting the Hubei medical team all the children to participate in the secondary school entrance examination, will be given 20 points preferential admission.

I usually pay more attention to the innovative development of enterprises, know country garden in agriculture, construction robots, robot cooking. Didn't think it would come in handy this time.

On the 16th, at the isolation point of the state-funded college in Hubei Province, the medical staff in the front line of the battle ate steaming hot pot rice. "Cook" is the first batch of Country Garden donated to Wuhan through the Guoqiang Foundation, from the 16-hour overnight transport, February 15 in the face of a blizzard to put into use, only 36 hours.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
The Country Garden allocated a total of $200 million on New Year's eve and February 13 to set up the COVID-19.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
In the future, I hope to be able to see this "small kiosk" in the streets and Parks of Wuhan, not only the rice pot, but also hot and dry noodles.

04

People's Daily helps find people to sell vegetables

On Feb. 4, People's Daily published a special "soliciting" message on its various new media platforms. Internet users can submit the information they have learned about the four categories of people (confirmed, suspected, close contacts, and fever that can not be ruled out) who have not yet received the information of seeking help for treatment in isolation through email, message, etc. , the platforms will do everything possible to help those who need help. "people good doctor" APP also overnight emergency online form submission function, to facilitate the submission of information for help.

Now the People's Daily is selling vegetables for farmers:

If you have any farmers or businesses who are affected by the outbreak, please provide us with relevant information and we will do our best to help you.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Good press in China.

The new pneumonia, so that China's online enterprises to get more rapid development.

Since February, more than 30,000 people have come to Taobao every day to open new stores, more than 20 percent of them from offline stores. In addition, manufacturers directly on Taobao live sales volume increased 50% year-on-year, of which, apparel, beauty, home 3 industries of the most active online shop live.

The number of searches for baked goods on takeout has increased 100 fold. Coriander with close to million sales and potatoes together, as a "national vegetable. ". The post-90s still firmly occupy the main force position of the take-out platform with 53% proportion. They pushed instant noodles, dried beans, beverages, puffed foods and leafy vegetables into the top five list of items sold over the past month.

As the fight against the epidemic continues, Zhejiang is once again throwing out "hard core" operations: Charter flights, high-speed Rail, Free pick-up workers to return to work.

On the 16th, the Hangzhou municipal government launched a high-speed train for employees in Guizhou and Sichuan provinces, where the epidemic is relatively stable and employment is concentrated.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
On the 19th, Huzhou, Jiaxing and other places organized charter flights from Sichuan and Yunnan to pick up nearly 300 employees back to work.

WHO'S GONNA pay for it? The Jiashan County government pays two-thirds of the cost of a charter flight for staff returning to their jobs, and companies pay a third of the cost.

Zhejiang resumed work rate is highest, fight epidemic also to do well, did not lose a person, return long-term export cadre, really great.

When Wuhan uses various methods to contact the residents, Zhejiang has already promoted the health code comprehensively, the efficiency is extremely high.

After Hangzhou took the lead in launching health code nationwide, this mode of access was rapidly extended to the whole of Zhejiang Province. Health codes for Huzhou, Jinhua, Lishui, Ningbo, Quzhou, Shaoxing, Taizhou, Taizhou, the city of Hangzhou and Taizhou are online today, allowing residents to get their health codes from a mobile payment service called paypal, code-based access.

Health Code Implementation of "Green Code, red code, Yellow Code" three-color dynamic management, and nail business to resume the application platform to open: Show Green Code, Light Code Access; Show Red Code and Yellow Code, need self-isolation and Healthy Punch card, it will be converted to Green Code when the conditions are met. A large number of workers back to work in Alipay to apply for Health Code, Hangzhou Health Code Online first-day visits that reached 10 million.

This method can be extended to Hubei.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
National Sun Yat-sen University students from Hubei Province received a message from the school saying: "To support you and your family through difficult times, the school has given you 1,000 yuan in condolence money. " The Students said the school quietly made the donation without prior notice, "hard to hide the feeling and gratitude. ".

Seeing this kind of care, netizens have asked: Did your school send it? Some people say they don't envy mask delivery anymore.

Speaking of college, many parents can not help but envy a girl in Wuhan.

Cao Wenfang, a Wuhan born doctoral student at the University of Padua, could not return to Italy to defend her thesis because of the epidemic, therefore, after discussion, the University of Padua decided to hold a special defense ceremony for Wuhan Female Students-video Defense. Cao Wenfang successfully defended her doctoral thesis in her home in Wuhan on Thursday, earning her doctorate from the University of Padua. Wuhan girl praised by Foreign Teachers "full of hope and perseverance. ".

There are such sensible children, but also "pit mother" children.

At a press conference on Monday afternoon, Pang Xinghuo, deputy director of the COVID-19, described a painstaking epidemiological investigation.

An old man has two sons. The old man lives with his eldest son in Beijing. The younger son and his family lived in Wuhan for a long time. The younger son's family heard that Wuhan was to be "closed" , and did everything possible to drive to Changsha. Then, the younger son of a family from Changsha by plane to Beijing, to Beijing to take a taxi directly to the mother and brother of a family.

And as usual go out shopping, buy medicine, take express delivery, and even the management of the community chat, ask how to deal with the Beijing card.

As a result, the old mother had a fever. To the hospital, the elderly or not to tell the truth, they do not admit that someone from Wuhan to Beijing. The CDC kept asking, but the old man wouldn't talk. Finally, in cooperation with the public security personnel, in the disease control personnel repeated cross-examination, they told the truth.

The youngest son tested positive for nucleic acid in the lab.

If you hurt someone, you hurt mom.

Hang in there.
